Let $$F \subseteq X^{(k)}$$ (a layer of the [[Power set]] of $$X$$) be a $$k$$-uniform family of subsets of $$X$$ (that is they all have the same size). The ''(lower) shadow'' $$\partial F$$ of $$F$$ is

: $$\partial F : = \{B \in X^{(k-1)} : B \subseteq A \text{ for some } A \in F \}$$